

Dependencies for JUnit and Mockito are listed below
	<dependencies>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>junit</groupId>
            <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
            <version>4.12</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
        <dependency>
            <groupId>org.mockito</groupId>
            <artifactId>mockito-all</artifactId>
            <version>1.10.19</version>
            <scope>test</scope>
        </dependency>
	</dependencies>

Stub - A stub is a class that comes with preprogrammed return values .
Mock - 

Drawbacks Of Stub:
---------------------
1. complex code - if we want to write a test to check the method to verify the zero results then we need to write similar testRetrieveTasksRelatedToSpring test methods and we need to change in stub class also
2. Test cases couple tightly due to the hard-coding of data.
		if we add a method in interface, then immediatly stub class will fail
		

 